Need explicit ./ in latex2man -t ./pstoedit.trans

This is because . has been removed from the latex2man include file search path.
So without it:

$ cd doc; make pstoedit.1 pstoedit.htm

latex2man -t pstoedit.trans -M pstoedit.tex pstoedit.1
do "pstoedit.trans" failed, '.' is no longer in @INC; did you mean do "./pstoedit.trans"? at /usr/bin/latex2man line 2010.
Error in line 360: no such macro: \TeX
Makefile:594: recipe for target 'pstoedit.1' failed

latex2man -t pstoedit.trans -H pstoedit.tex pstoedit.htm
